The  University of Illinois  at
Urbana-Champaign received a $100 million pledge from the
Grainger Foundation to support the schoolâ€™s College of
Engineering.  The gift was made in memory of William W. Grainger, founder
of W.W. Grainger Inc., a hardware supply distributor based in
 Lake Forest , Illinois, Chancellor Phyllis Wise said in a
 statement  yesterday. Grainger graduated from the university in
1919.  Part of the gift will create an endowment for chairs and
professorships at the engineering school, which has more than
10,700 enrolled undergraduate and graduate students.  To contact the reporter on this story: Lisa Wolfson at 
